  <prompt>
    Extend the playbook canvas node-config schema with two new fields: `destination`
    (enum: `chat` | `workspace` | `form-prefill` | `side-effect`) and `widgetType`
    (string; required when `destination = workspace`). These fields are PER-NODE
    (per-playbook routing) â€” they are the Q5-re-shape counterpart to action-level
    `outputSchema` (task 030). The existing `DeliverOutput` node executor reads these
    fields at runtime and routes the action's output accordingly. The executor itself is
    NOT modified (NFR-08 binding: 11 production node executors preserved).

    Determine the concrete storage surface from `playbook-architecture.md`. Playbook nodes
    are typically stored as JSON in `sprk_analysisplaybook.sprk_nodesjson` (or sibling
    column). If the canvas schema is a JSON contract validated at write time, extend the
    contract (TypeScript / JSON Schema interface definition) and apply optional defaults
    for backward compatibility â€” existing nodes without the fields default to `chat`
    destination (current behavior). If the canvas schema is a separate Dataverse entity
    (e.g., `sprk_analysisplaybooknode`), add two columns following the existing pattern.
    Document which surface applies in task notes.

    Schema change to a production-shape data contract is a CLAUDE.md Confirmation Trigger.
    The agent MUST pause and confirm the surface + the migration approach with the user
    before proceeding. Migration MUST be idempotent + backward-compatible (existing
    playbooks continue to work). BFF publish-size impact: schema-only addition; expect
    near-zero delta (verify if any TypeScript contracts ship in BFF binaries).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Senior platform engineer with deep familiarity with the
    playbook canvas data model, `DeliverOutput` node executor, and the existing scope /
    playbook entity schema. Comfortable applying schema changes via the
    `dataverse-create-schema` skill OR by extending JSON Schema contract definitions in
    BFF + frontend, depending on which surface applies.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Playbook node config schema is extended with `destination` (enum) + `widgetType`
    (string, conditionally required) fields. The extension is committed to the repo; if
    Dataverse-backed, migration is idempotent + deployed to Spaarke Dev; if
    JSON-Schema-backed, the contract is updated in source + validated by existing tests.
    Existing playbooks continue to work â€” nodes without the fields behave as today
    (default destination = `chat`). Downstream tasks 032-035 set `destination` per node
    for the 4 migrated actions; task 042 (CapabilityRouter dedup) relies on this surface.
  </goal>

