  <context>
    <background>
      Q5 re-shape this session split output routing cleanly: action OUTPUT shape (intrinsic;
      task 030) is independent of playbook-canvas ROUTING decisions (per-playbook;
      this task). A playbook author can compose the same Summarize action into two
      different playbooks â€” one routing to chat, one routing to a workspace tab â€” without
      changing the action. The `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (tasks 040, 041) becomes
      schema-aware by reading the action's `outputSchema` AND respecting the node's
      `widgetType`. `DeliverOutput` reads `destination` to pick the surface.

      The CapabilityRouter dedup (task 042) needs a canonical "where does this output go"
      surface to enforce one-route-per-intent. Putting that surface on the node config
      (this task) cleanly separates routing from intrinsic shape.
    </background>
